on of exilic and diasporic identities. Particular attention is given to the inscription of the Holocaust and of Jewish memory in her films.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directors. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh  aAkerman's filmmaking.  aAmerican structuralist film.  aChantal Akerman.  aJewish Polish immigrants.  aautobiography.  aavant-garde work.  acinema.  acontemporary directors.  afiction.  anew hedonism.  aperformance art.  apost-Holocaust sensibility.  apost-feminist sensibility.  apost-war sensibility.1 aSchmid, Marion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614121740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141217423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141217/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles